Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a
large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop two thirds of the @garlic cloves{3} (unpeeled) into a small piece
of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it. Roast the parcel
on the baking tray of wedges until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Peel and grate the remaining garlic (or use a #garlic press{}).

Slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} down through the middle (but not all the way
through).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a spoon to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard
any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment
after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the grated garlic and @chipotle paste{20%g} to the beef. Stir-fry for
~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1}, @beef stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and
@water{75%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts).

Bring the chilli up to the boil, then reduce the heat slightly and simmer until
thickened, ~{7-8%minutes}.

== Roasted Garlic Slaw ==

Once the garlic has roasted and cooled, cut the end with #scissors{},
squeeze it out of the skin into a #medium bowl{}. Mash with a #fork{}.

Mix in the @mayonnaise{32%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the
@coleslaw mix{120%g} to the bowl and mix to coat. Set your slaw aside.

Pop the brioche buns into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, spoon the beef chilli into the buns and place on your
plates. Sprinkle over the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}.

Serve the garlic slaw and wedges alongside.

> Enjoy!

> This Chipotle Beef Chilli in a Bun and Wedges with Mature Cheddar Cheese is bursting
> full of flavours and makes the perfect dinner night option from HelloFresh. Cook
> up a fresh start!